commit.message: Release 0.5.2

Initialize comp_data to NULL in drpm_apply()

On exit, this function will free comp_data, so at least ensure it's
initialized to NULL so free() does not SIGSEGV.

Fixes: #5

Signed-off-by: David Cantrell <dcantrell@redhat.com>

Avoid long obsolete librpm API use

headerCopyLoad() was removed from rpm 4.19, this is compatible to
rpm 4.10 (so works even on RHEL 7).

C99 compatibility fix for drpm_write.c

Include <string.h> for various string functions.  This avoids
implicit function declarations and resulting build failures with
future compilers.

Fix: set the actual value, not the pointer. (RhBug:1968594)

This fixes the previous commit, all the reasoning still applies.

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1968594

For rpms without any files return file count 0 (RhBug:1968594)

When the processed rpm file doesn't have any files `rpm_get_file_info`
doesn't consider it an error therefore it should set `count_ret` to 0.

Otherwise it can lead to crashes when the caller of `rpm_get_file_info`
doesn't zero initialize the count variable. Such as in:
`parse_cpio_from_rpm_filedata`

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1968594

commit.message:
Fix SIGSEGV when an errors occurs in `rpm_get_file_info` (RhBug:1968594)

`rpm_get_file_info` already cleans up `files` array in its error
handling doing it again in the caller (`parse_cpio_from_rpm_filedata`)
results in a crash

Since we are at the begging of the `parse_cpio_from_rpm_filedata` and
there is nothing to clean up yet there is no need to `goto` to the error
handling, we can return directly.

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1968594

commit.message: spec: Fix building with new cmake macros

Use <sys/sysmacros.h> instead of <linux/kdev_t.h>.

Use a glibc header file and the major(3), minor(3), and makedev(3)
macros instead of the Linux-specific MAJOR, MINOR, and MAKEDEV ones.
This fixes the build on the GNU Hurd.
Release 0.5.0

Hide the internal library symbols.

Programs linking against the drpm library should not be able to see
any symbols other than the drpm_*() functions declared in the drpm.h
header file.
Fix a memory leak on invalid input.

spec: Enable zstd support for RHEL 8

Since RHEL 8.2, zstd is now in RHEL and rpm is compiled with zstd
support.
